experiences.

00:03:25.720 --> 00:03:29.330
And I am also very much
aware and affirming

00:03:29.330 --> 00:03:32.695
of the LGBTQ community.

00:03:32.695 --> 00:03:34.070
And the question
is, how does one

00:03:34.070 --> 00:03:36.590
do it when you take
scripture, as I

00:03:36.590 --> 00:03:39.210
do, very, very, very seriously?

00:03:39.210 --> 00:03:42.500
Well, first thing is,
to remind ourselves

00:03:42.500 --> 00:03:45.110
that it is the word of
God, not the scriptures.

00:03:45.110 --> 00:03:48.920
In fact, in the
30,000 scriptures

00:03:48.920 --> 00:03:50.360
that are in the
bible, it does not

00:03:50.360 --> 00:03:51.680
claim itself to be inerrant.

00:03:51.680 --> 00:03:54.080
It claims itself to
be always good for--

00:03:54.080 --> 00:03:57.830
profitable for reproof,
profitable for instruction,

00:03:57.830 --> 00:03:59.000
profitable for changing.

00:03:59.000 --> 00:04:01.730
It's important, but
it also understands

00:04:01.730 --> 00:04:05.060
that the spirit of the living
God and the experience of Jesus

00:04:05.060 --> 00:04:08.780
is what, in fact, is the
important part of scripture,

00:04:08.780 --> 00:04:10.640
and important part
of interpretation.

00:04:10.640 --> 00:04:13.220
Because remember,
unless someone was there

00:04:13.220 --> 00:04:16.100
when scripture was written,
all of it is interpretation.

00:04:16.100 --> 00:04:18.769
So when someone says
to me, well, this

00:04:18.769 --> 00:04:21.279
is what the bible says, and
I know it, and this is it,

00:04:21.279 --> 00:04:22.670
then there's one or two options.

00:04:22.670 --> 00:04:25.190
They're either
actually just unaware

00:04:25.190 --> 00:04:27.972
of their own social
location, or it could be

00:04:27.972 --> 00:04:29.180
that they're manipulating me.

00:04:29.180 --> 00:04:32.810
Or it could be, literally,
that somehow they

00:04:32.810 --> 00:04:36.260
want to take their stance
and their understanding

00:04:36.260 --> 00:04:38.330
of the bible, their
understanding of faith,

00:04:38.330 --> 00:04:39.860
and lay it on me.

00:04:39.860 --> 00:04:41.760
Because I'm an
evangelical, I can say,

00:04:41.760 --> 00:04:44.210
you know what, you have
your relationship with God.

00:04:44.210 --> 00:04:48.960
And I respect that, and
let us reason together.

00:04:48.960 --> 00:04:51.470
But at the same time, let us
also come together, and look

00:04:51.470 --> 00:04:53.810
and see what the scriptures
say in the context

00:04:53.810 --> 00:04:56.000
of the witness of
Christ, and the context

00:04:56.000 --> 00:04:57.470
of the witness of God.

00:04:57.470 --> 00:05:00.860
Because one always has
to ask, what is going on,

00:05:00.860 --> 00:05:05.630
and how is it a religiously
OK thing to exclude someone?

00:05:05.630 --> 00:05:07.790
I also come from the--

00:05:07.790 --> 00:05:12.350
Steven Biko of South Africa says
that diversity is not something

00:05:12.350 --> 00:05:13.880
that is accidental to God.

00:05:13.880 --> 00:05:16.760
It is the intentionality
of God to make it diverse,

00:05:16.760 --> 00:05:19.670
so that in the diversity
we may discover,

00:05:19.670 --> 00:05:23.090
not just our own path,
but the path of God.

00:05:23.090 --> 00:05:25.040
So in other words,
if God is not simply

00:05:25.040 --> 00:05:29.030
trying to affirm ourselves,
but God is actually

00:05:29.030 --> 00:05:31.040
trying to expand ourselves.

00:05:31.040 --> 00:05:33.890
And finally, I wanted to
say one of the things I say

00:05:33.890 --> 00:05:35.790
around an altar all the time.

00:05:35.790 --> 00:05:38.900
It is not interesting that
people believe in God.

00:05:38.900 --> 00:05:43.290
Because look, if
the sunrise doesn't

00:05:43.290 --> 00:05:47.000
make you believe in God,
then I don't know what will.

00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:49.770
What is interesting
is, Jesus comes to say,

00:05:49.770 --> 00:05:52.130
no, it is not that
I am so great.

00:05:52.130 --> 00:05:55.520
But I am come to tell you
that I believe in you--

00:05:55.520 --> 00:05:59.420
that there is in your humanity
something so powerful,

00:05:59.420 --> 00:06:02.540
so amazing, that I have
created an image of God.

00:06:02.540 --> 00:06:04.700
That when you
accept that and live

00:06:04.700 --> 00:06:07.710
that in a collaborative
experience,

00:06:07.710 --> 00:06:09.860
you come to know me
in a different way.

00:06:09.860 --> 00:06:11.960
Because that is the incarnation.

00:06:11.960 --> 00:06:15.410
Other than that, all we have is
another religious expression.

00:06:15.410 --> 00:06:19.070
The incarnation, which is Jesus,
makes it mean that the human

00:06:19.070 --> 00:06:21.560
experience-- the
diversity itself--

00:06:21.560 --> 00:06:23.810
has to be something
that is not accidental,

00:06:23.810 --> 00:06:26.870
or something that is
managed, or that is something

00:06:26.870 --> 00:06:28.340
that we have to live through--

00:06:28.340 --> 00:06:31.220
but actually is the gift of
God to the people of God.

00:06:31.220 --> 00:06:34.110
And it is in that gift
that we celebrate today,

00:06:34.110 --> 00:06:35.610
and we hear these stories.

00:06:35.610 --> 00:06:38.150
It's in that gift that
we allow ourselves

00:06:38.150 --> 00:06:40.670
to have all kinds of diversity.

00:06:40.670 --> 00:06:44.180
And the same time to say,
truth is in that diversity.

00:06:44.180 --> 00:06:48.320
And finally, that truth is
not relative, it is eternal.

00:06:48.320 --> 00:06:53.290
But what is relative, is our
understanding, and our growing

00:06:53.290 --> 00:06:55.479
to what God is saying.

00:06:55.479 --> 00:06:57.020
For instance, in
the Catholic Church,

00:06:57.020 --> 00:06:58.930
that's what Vatican
II was all about.

00:06:58.930 --> 00:07:02.750
And as we move in prayer--
because other than it,

00:07:02.750 --> 00:07:03.610
why pray?

00:07:03.610 --> 00:07:05.330
If the only thing you
want to do is say--

00:07:05.330 --> 00:07:07.730
if prayer is only the
recitation of saying,

00:07:07.730 --> 00:07:11.960
God give me stuff,
then that's not

00:07:11.960 --> 00:07:13.970
what I experience as prayer.

00:07:13.970 --> 00:07:16.280
Prayer is also,
God show me stuff,

00:07:16.280 --> 00:07:19.310
and God, show me how to expand.

00:07:19.310 --> 00:07:22.670
When we say in the psalms,
God, enlarge yourself,

00:07:22.670 --> 00:07:24.530
God can't get any bigger.

00:07:24.530 --> 00:07:26.300
So it's not about God being--

00:07:26.300 --> 00:07:28.910
it is meaning a
large vision of God.

00:07:28.910 --> 00:07:32.420
And enlarging our vision of
God is how God becomes larger.

00:07:32.420 --> 00:07:35.990
So today, I know there are
folks who have differences.

00:07:35.990 --> 00:07:40.040
But we come in this place to
say, Lord, enlarge yourself,

00:07:40.040 --> 00:07:42.530
which is to enlarge
our vision, so that we

00:07:42.530 --> 00:07:45.650
may see you as you
want us to see you,

00:07:45.650 --> 00:07:47.730
not as is comfortable to see.

00:07:47.730 --> 00:07:49.260
With that, I'm through.

00:07:49.260 --> 00:07:50.009
Go ahead.

00:07:54.500 --> 00:07:59.750
ANNANDA BARCLAY: So when
it comes to scripture,

00:07:59.750 --> 00:08:02.720
I go from the two greatest--
the two commandments Christ

00:08:02.720 --> 00:08:06.710
taught us, to love God
with all your heart, soul,

00:08:06.710 --> 00:08:12.242
and mind, body, and also to
love your neighbor as yourself.

00:08:12.242 --> 00:08:13.950
Those are the two
fundamental scriptures.

00:08:13.950 --> 00:08:19.710
So when we're talking about
loving somebody and Christ,

00:08:19.710 --> 00:08:23.010
who we all understand to be
fully human and fully divine,

00:08:23.010 --> 00:08:26.370
and yet you are made
in the image of God,

00:08:26.370 --> 00:08:29.490
then if Christ is the Son of
God and you are children of God,

00:08:29.490 --> 00:08:34.380
does that not make us all
fully human and fully divine?

00:08:34.380 --> 00:08:37.740
And if we're to go there
and talk about our faith,

00:08:37.740 --> 00:08:39.840
and how we enact
our faith, how we're

00:08:39.840 --> 00:08:41.159
disciples within our faith--

00:08:43.919 --> 00:08:46.020
what do we mean
when we say faith?

00:08:46.020 --> 00:08:48.600
And what do we mean when
we're talking about loving

00:08:48.600 --> 00:08:51.370
our neighbor as ourselves?

00:08:51.370 --> 00:08:53.760
So if we look at
faith, in many ways

00:08:53.760 --> 00:08:58.030
faith is not just
faith in God out there,

00:08:58.030 --> 00:09:01.410
this God that's in the
heavens and the universes

00:09:01.410 --> 00:09:03.150
upon universes.

00:09:03.150 --> 00:09:05.970
Faith is also in
the divinity that

00:09:05.970 --> 00:09:07.650
is in each and every one of us.

00:09:07.650 --> 00:09:13.200
Faith is in the living God that
exists within your neighbor

00:09:13.200 --> 00:09:14.850
and yourself.

00:09:14.850 --> 00:09:18.600
And so when we talk
about specific subject

00:09:18.600 --> 00:09:22.860
of LGBTQ inclusion in the
church, what we're talking

00:09:22.860 --> 00:09:24.780
about is, are you
willing to acknowledge

00:09:24.780 --> 00:09:29.130
the divinity, the image
of God in your neighbor?

00:09:29.130 --> 00:09:30.987
And if you take
away that divinity--

00:09:30.987 --> 00:09:32.070
you're not taking it away.

00:09:32.070 --> 00:09:33.778
You don't have the
power to take it away.

00:09:33.778 --> 00:09:37.110
But if you try to
mute it, or deny it,

00:09:37.110 --> 00:09:40.140
are you not also denying
the divinity in yourself?

00:09:40.140 --> 00:09:44.850
You are funneling, excluding
God, instead of expanding.

00:09:44.850 --> 00:09:46.350
Another theological
approach to that

00:09:46.350 --> 00:09:49.695
would be Octavia
Butler, a famous African

00:09:49.695 --> 00:09:51.120
American female--

00:09:51.120 --> 00:09:53.240
I believe she was queer--

00:09:53.240 --> 00:09:55.050
sci-fi novelist.

00:09:55.050 --> 00:09:57.900
And her theology
is, God is change,

00:09:57.900 --> 00:09:59.190
because change is inevitable.

00:09:59.190 --> 00:10:03.350
That is one thing I would
assume Google knows very well.

00:10:03.350 --> 00:10:05.580
AI is a big deal.

00:10:05.580 --> 00:10:09.000
Change constantly, there is no
sameness-- so in the same way,

00:10:09.000 --> 00:10:13.350
our expansion and understanding
of God must change as we grow

00:10:13.350 --> 00:10:15.030
and spiritually mature.

00:10:15.030 --> 00:10:20.430
A sign of spiritual stagnancy
is sticking our heels in.

00:10:20.430 --> 00:10:24.510
And if we look at Christ's
ministry in all four gospels,

00:10:24.510 --> 00:10:29.340
Christ is constantly being
changed by those he encounters.

00:10:29.340 --> 00:10:31.920
He does not stay the
same in his ministry.

00:10:31.920 --> 00:10:35.130
His divinity is the
same, so is yours.

00:10:35.130 --> 00:10:38.250
His humanity is the
same, so is yours.

00:10:38.250 --> 00:10:40.830
But he's willing to be
changed and transformed,

00:10:40.830 --> 00:10:43.200
and in turn his ministry grows.

00:10:43.200 --> 00:10:47.700
And we know him
2000-years-plus, to this day.

00:10:47.700 --> 00:10:51.300
So that's more of
the approach that I

00:10:51.300 --> 00:10:54.270
take with this as an
overall expansion,

00:10:54.270 --> 00:10:57.630
and we'll funnel it
down with questions.

00:10:57.630 --> 00:11:02.460
But I would encourage you all
to look at your own divinity,

00:11:02.460 --> 00:11:07.810
and to see the divinity of
others, because it's important.

00:11:07.810 --> 00:11:11.790
And if you miss it, you miss God
in the everyday interactions.

00:11:11.790 --> 00:11:13.830
And it becomes easy
to other somebody.

00:11:13.830 --> 00:11:16.840
It becomes easy to
discard somebody.

00:11:16.840 --> 00:11:19.746
It becomes easy to deny
another their humanity, which

00:11:19.746 --> 00:11:22.245
is their inherent right for the
simple fact that they exist.

