I have a twin sister, so
we had lots of boyfriends,

00:13:11.440 --> 00:13:13.970
we had lots of people
around us and so on.

00:13:13.970 --> 00:13:16.330
But the most
important thing was I

00:13:16.330 --> 00:13:20.410
knew, even in
marrying Jimmy Spahr,

00:13:20.410 --> 00:13:24.490
that the deepest place
inside of me was not met.

00:13:24.490 --> 00:13:28.750
And I call it that
God place deep inside.

00:13:28.750 --> 00:13:32.020
And then when I realized--
when I went from oh, my god,

00:13:32.020 --> 00:13:36.350
to thank you, God, it was
like, wow, this is fabulous.

00:13:36.350 --> 00:13:37.490
I can be myself.

00:13:37.490 --> 00:13:39.340
I can really be who I am.

00:13:39.340 --> 00:13:43.030
And with that then, these are
the other questions that came.

00:13:43.030 --> 00:13:47.260
Well, if people
are off about this,

00:13:47.260 --> 00:13:51.850
and they only see us as
mythology or stereotypes,

00:13:51.850 --> 00:13:55.570
then who else is
being stereotyped?

00:13:55.570 --> 00:13:57.430
Who else is being told--

00:13:57.430 --> 00:14:01.360
you know, how am I being duped?

00:14:01.360 --> 00:14:04.720
Or how am I complicit
with a culture that

00:14:04.720 --> 00:14:07.720
stereotypes and
labels and says, this

00:14:07.720 --> 00:14:10.000
is what it is to
be this or that?

00:14:10.000 --> 00:14:14.230
And with that, not only
did God expand within me,

00:14:14.230 --> 00:14:15.790
but I expanded.

00:14:15.790 --> 00:14:18.880
And it was this
tremendous meeting

00:14:18.880 --> 00:14:24.310
of who God is within us, and
around us, and beside us.

00:14:24.310 --> 00:14:26.360
So then when I
came out, thinking

00:14:26.360 --> 00:14:28.360
the church would surely
love us, because then we

00:14:28.360 --> 00:14:31.470
can be who we are,
the church says, no.

00:14:31.470 --> 00:14:34.060
I'm like, what?

00:14:34.060 --> 00:14:36.520
We're finally who we
are, we can finally--

00:14:36.520 --> 00:14:39.530
we can give our gifts fully,
we don't have to be afraid.

00:14:39.530 --> 00:14:41.230
We don't have to hide.

00:14:41.230 --> 00:14:43.060
This is an amazing
thing that happens,

00:14:43.060 --> 00:14:44.570
and then they don't want us.

00:14:44.570 --> 00:14:47.970
So I think the church
had to learn from us,

00:14:47.970 --> 00:14:51.190
it's to meet us--

00:14:51.190 --> 00:14:54.100
it's to meet who we are
as LGBTQ Christians.

00:14:54.100 --> 00:14:55.620
It's to see who we are.

00:14:55.620 --> 00:14:58.120
It's to hear our life,
it's to hear our faith.

00:14:58.120 --> 00:14:59.650
This is how we change.

00:14:59.650 --> 00:15:01.177
I mean, I've been
in so many debates

00:15:01.177 --> 00:15:02.760
around scripture,
and so on like that.

00:15:02.760 --> 00:15:05.140
But when you meet
us, and you see us,

00:15:05.140 --> 00:15:09.370
and you meet someone like
Annanda, you feel this--

00:15:09.370 --> 00:15:12.550
you begin to hear that we
too are people of faith.

00:15:12.550 --> 00:15:15.850
We too are people that have
the same struggles, that

00:15:15.850 --> 00:15:19.750
have the same things that we're
looking for, the same dreams.

00:15:19.750 --> 00:15:25.840
So it's in that way I find
that scriptural debate has

00:15:25.840 --> 00:15:28.810
been something that
I find is heady,

00:15:28.810 --> 00:15:34.420
and it moves away from the
personhood of who Christ

00:15:34.420 --> 00:15:35.830
is within us.

00:15:35.830 --> 00:15:39.910
And with that, that then breaks
us away from one another.

00:15:39.910 --> 00:15:42.970
So throughout the
country as I traveled,

00:15:42.970 --> 00:15:45.070
it was things like this
that people would say.

00:15:45.070 --> 00:15:48.690
They would say, well, God,
you really can preach,

00:15:48.690 --> 00:15:51.980
as though we wouldn't
preach from the text.

00:15:51.980 --> 00:15:55.450
And meeting people
for the first time--

00:15:55.450 --> 00:15:58.780
people hearing gay
is good, and you

00:15:58.780 --> 00:16:01.000
are who you are because of God.

00:16:01.000 --> 00:16:02.020
Can you imagine?

00:16:02.020 --> 00:16:04.510
We went into one
church in Alabama.

00:16:04.510 --> 00:16:08.110
And you knew every LGBTQ
person in the place,

00:16:08.110 --> 00:16:10.360
because they laid their
heads down and wept,

00:16:10.360 --> 00:16:13.480
because no one had
ever said to them,

00:16:13.480 --> 00:16:17.010
this is such a good thing,
this is such a God thing,

00:16:17.010 --> 00:16:18.460
of who you are.

00:16:18.460 --> 00:16:22.420
It is in that kind of
travel as we moved around,

00:16:22.420 --> 00:16:24.610
as we moved in churches
where people were

00:16:24.610 --> 00:16:27.060
afraid to say who they were.

00:16:27.060 --> 00:16:28.990
And so they'd say
things like this--

00:16:28.990 --> 00:16:30.970
well, thanks, Janie,
for coming, but there's

00:16:30.970 --> 00:16:32.650
no other gay people here.

00:16:32.650 --> 00:16:37.390
And there was always someone who
stood in the church and said,

00:16:37.390 --> 00:16:39.840
but I'm here, I'm here.

00:16:39.840 --> 00:16:41.950
And they go, Sally?

00:16:41.950 --> 00:16:46.050
Our Sally, our one who's our
deacon, our most faithful

00:16:46.050 --> 00:16:46.950
person?

00:16:46.950 --> 00:16:51.300
It happened in every faith
community that we went to.

00:16:51.300 --> 00:16:54.690
It happened in Iowa
with grandmothers

00:16:54.690 --> 00:16:57.300
who said, we've been
waiting for you to come,

00:16:57.300 --> 00:17:00.180
because I have a wonderful
lesbian granddaughter,

00:17:00.180 --> 00:17:04.290
and I've wanted to say it
out loud to my whole church.

00:17:04.290 --> 00:17:07.500
It's meeting people, it's
hearing their stories,

00:17:07.500 --> 00:17:10.280
it's feeling who they are.

00:17:10.280 --> 00:17:15.060
It isn't-- I would say, who
do people think Jesus was?

00:17:15.060 --> 00:17:17.160
He was a radical.

00:17:17.160 --> 00:17:18.819
He was a radical rebel.

00:17:18.819 --> 00:17:22.470
He took on people who said
that women were not equal.

00:17:22.470 --> 00:17:24.270
He changed the theme of that.

00:17:24.270 --> 00:17:26.960
He talked about Samaritans
that are different.

00:17:26.960 --> 00:17:29.520
And he said, there they
are in the realm of God.

00:17:29.520 --> 00:17:30.510
They're part of God.

00:17:30.510 --> 00:17:33.810
Everything that he did
challenged the status quo

00:17:33.810 --> 00:17:35.340
of the time.

00:17:35.340 --> 00:17:36.510
That's what he did.

00:17:36.510 --> 00:17:39.720
He was a radical rabbi.

00:17:39.720 --> 00:17:42.930
And so I always thought,
well, isn't that

00:17:42.930 --> 00:17:44.850
what we're supposed to be doing?

00:17:44.850 --> 00:17:47.250
Aren't we supposed
to be challenging

00:17:47.250 --> 00:17:52.530
these systems of oppression
that keep us from one another?

00:17:52.530 --> 00:17:55.440
So that's, I think, our job--

00:17:55.440 --> 00:17:57.930
is to live into
that, and challenge

00:17:57.930 --> 00:18:01.383
everything in which they say,
these people are that way--

00:18:01.383 --> 00:18:02.210
no.

00:18:02.210 --> 00:18:04.834
And I'll tell you
one more story.

00:18:04.834 --> 00:18:06.750
A person called me on
the phone and they said,

00:18:06.750 --> 00:18:07.650
are you Janie Spahr?

00:18:07.650 --> 00:18:08.316
And I said, yes.

00:18:08.316 --> 00:18:11.400
He said, do you know that
there is a complaint being made

00:18:11.400 --> 00:18:13.740
against you in Philadelphia?

00:18:13.740 --> 00:18:14.812
I said no, no I didn't.

00:18:14.812 --> 00:18:17.020
He said, you mean nobody
called you to tell you this?

00:18:17.020 --> 00:18:18.420
I said no, nobody called me.

00:18:18.420 --> 00:18:24.010
He said, well, then, I
want to know who you are.

00:18:24.010 --> 00:18:25.810
I want to hear your faith.

00:18:25.810 --> 00:18:28.650
I want to hear how you
love, who you love.

00:18:28.650 --> 00:18:31.680
I want to know who you are.

00:18:31.680 --> 00:18:34.440
And we had this
amazing conversation.

00:18:34.440 --> 00:18:37.150
And he went back to that
governing body and he said,

00:18:37.150 --> 00:18:39.180
how many of you
know Janie Spahr?

00:18:39.180 --> 00:18:41.880
How many of you called her
and asked her about her faith?

00:18:41.880 --> 00:18:43.960
How many of you know who she is?

00:18:43.960 --> 00:18:45.810
Well, I do.

00:18:45.810 --> 00:18:49.080
I called her, and I know
her, and I talked to her.

00:18:49.080 --> 00:18:54.070
And I'm voting for her, and
god, I'd wish you'd do the same.

00:18:54.070 --> 00:18:57.390
It's that kind of change
that has to happen.

00:18:57.390 --> 00:19:01.140
And then when you watch people
that are so hurt by the church,

00:19:01.140 --> 00:19:04.440
or by community--

00:19:04.440 --> 00:19:08.100
the church has been the greatest
perpetrator of injustice

00:19:08.100 --> 00:19:10.680
against LGBTQ people.

00:19:10.680 --> 00:19:14.580
So those of us that are
still in the church, you see,

00:19:14.580 --> 00:19:18.960
are trying to spread this good
news of God's love for all.

00:19:18.960 --> 00:19:22.560
This is what we're trying to
do, because the church has been

00:19:22.560 --> 00:19:26.190
so unjust in labeling
and framing us

00:19:26.190 --> 00:19:28.680
as less than, as second class.

00:19:28.680 --> 00:19:29.970
So we're here.

00:19:29.970 --> 00:19:33.150
We're here, we're queer, and we
love that God made us this way.

00:19:33.150 --> 00:19:36.550
And this is why we've
come here, to say, yay.

00:19:36.550 --> 00:19:38.940
You know, this is
the realm of God

00:19:38.940 --> 00:19:41.250
that is so diverse
and so wonderful,

00:19:41.250 --> 00:19:46.950
so let's not bring it back
into this tight script.

00:19:46.950 --> 00:19:52.420
God is so magnificent,
and that's why we're here.

00:19:52.420 --> 00:19:53.872
Thanks for having us.

00:19:53.872 --> 00:19:55.830
FLOYD THOMPKINS: Wanted
to own one other thing,

00:19:55.830 --> 00:19:58.650
because as we're
sitting here, also,

00:19:58.650 --> 00:20:02.320
the other thing that happens
in scripture, I think--

00:20:02.320 --> 00:20:04.480
you know, there's also a
social location, right?

00:20:04.480 --> 00:20:06.235
I'm a black male and
you're like, well,

00:20:06.235 --> 00:20:08.610
you're black, [INAUDIBLE]
straight, why is this an issue?

00:20:08.610 --> 00:20:11.100
Because remember,
African Americans,

00:20:11.100 --> 00:20:13.340
when you say, we're scripture
and everything else,

00:20:13.340 --> 00:20:16.250
there's that scripture called
slaves, obey your master.

00:20:16.250 --> 00:20:20.350
Um, which kind of is
the deal for us, right?

00:20:20.350 --> 00:20:23.460
[LAUGHS] if everything
in this bible is true,

00:20:23.460 --> 00:20:28.530
and that scripture is
true, then not only

00:20:28.530 --> 00:20:30.970
is it a text of
terror, but the church

00:20:30.970 --> 00:20:33.640
becomes a terroristic
organization to us, right?

00:20:33.640 --> 00:20:35.640
And that's not who we've
experienced it, though.

00:20:35.640 --> 00:20:38.660
Because actually, the church
became the place of liberation

00:20:38.660 --> 00:20:39.600
in slavery.

00:20:39.600 --> 00:20:43.330
Because it begins-- it's a
place of affirming humanity.

00:20:43.330 --> 00:20:47.150
And so then, by definition,
we have to work in scripture.

00:20:47.150 --> 00:20:49.900
Then, you look at the Greek,
then you look at the Hebrew.

00:20:49.900 --> 00:20:52.290
Then, you look and say,
what is the heart of God?

00:20:52.290 --> 00:20:54.060
So I just wanted
to say that this

00:20:54.060 --> 00:20:56.160
is-- because one of
the pre-questions

00:20:56.160 --> 00:20:58.800
is like, well, you're changing
because times are changing.

00:20:58.800 --> 00:21:02.314
No, we're changing-- at
least I'm not, quite frankly.

00:21:02.314 --> 00:21:04.230
By being a person that
believe in Jesus Christ

00:21:04.230 --> 00:21:06.180
and open the bible and
seeing that scripture,

00:21:06.180 --> 00:21:07.710
I obviously--
that's the beginning

00:21:07.710 --> 00:21:08.668
of the point of change.

00:21:08.668 --> 00:21:11.280
Because that scripture
calls me in to look to say,

00:21:11.280 --> 00:21:14.000
is that true, and is that
representative of God?

00:21:14.000 --> 00:21:16.290
And if that's what God
is saying about us, then

00:21:16.290 --> 00:21:18.670
therefore this can't be true.

00:21:18.670 --> 00:21:21.090
But then, you look at the
context of that scripture.

00:21:21.090 --> 00:21:22.860
You look at the words
of that scripture,

00:21:22.860 --> 00:21:24.526
and then you see
something new, and then

00:21:24.526 --> 00:21:26.320
you start seeing
scripture that way.

00:21:26.320 --> 00:21:28.340
So I just wanted to
also own that there

00:21:28.340 --> 00:21:32.160
is some connectedness also to
the understanding of scripture,

00:21:32.160 --> 00:21:35.160
and I think sometimes that's
what social location is.

00:21:35.160 --> 00:21:37.600
I think women have to do
it very naturally also,

00:21:37.600 --> 00:21:40.620
if, in point of fact, you accept
some of the scriptures that

00:21:40.620 --> 00:21:44.430
says, only men can do this and
that must be what it means.

00:21:44.430 --> 00:21:46.500
Then, I think as
a woman Christian,

00:21:46.500 --> 00:21:48.300
there's going to be
some issues, saying,

00:21:48.300 --> 00:21:49.980
was this the God
I need to serve?

00:21:49.980 --> 00:21:52.360
That's not the Jesus
I fell in love with.

00:21:52.360 --> 00:21:57.600
So there is a different stake
that I come to scripture with.

00:21:57.600 --> 00:22:01.620
Because to love Jesus
and to be a black man,

00:22:01.620 --> 00:22:04.740
I am interacting with scripture
from that social location.

00:22:04.740 --> 00:22:07.150
So that may be a different
location from a white man.

00:22:07.150 --> 00:22:09.990
That may be a different
location from a person of color.

00:22:09.990 --> 00:22:13.050
But that location is
what I want to call into.

00:22:13.050 --> 00:22:15.510
And also, that blindness--

00:22:15.510 --> 00:22:18.062
there is a blindness to say,
I don't see why you just

00:22:18.062 --> 00:22:19.020
don't see it like that.

00:22:19.020 --> 00:22:23.121
Well, of course you won't,
because it works for you.

00:22:23.121 --> 00:22:24.370
But it doesn't work for Jesus.

00:22:24.370 --> 00:22:25.900
It didn't work for the--

00:22:25.900 --> 00:22:27.375
you know, that's
why people were--

00:22:27.375 --> 00:22:28.500
I got to watch my language.

00:22:28.500 --> 00:22:31.560
That's why people were
not happy with Jesus.

00:22:31.560 --> 00:22:33.900
Because let's face it,
he looked and said,

00:22:33.900 --> 00:22:37.620
yo, I hear what you're
saying, it's just not--

00:22:37.620 --> 00:22:39.810
and I got you, Paul.

00:22:39.810 --> 00:22:42.990
At least, I got you, Saul, but
you've got to become a Paul.

00:22:42.990 --> 00:22:47.220
And that means you're actually
going to have to evolve.

00:22:47.220 --> 00:22:50.520
Saul to Paul is about evolving.

00:22:50.520 --> 00:22:56.040
And so that's the Jesus
that calls us into this.

00:22:56.040 --> 00:23:01.770
It's not easy, it's not
necessarily comfortable,

00:23:01.770 --> 00:23:04.350
but it is absolutely faithful.

00:23:04.350 --> 00:23:05.940
It is what scripture does.

00:23:05.940 --> 00:23:07.897
And then to ask me
not to do it, is

00:23:07.897 --> 00:23:10.230
to then tell me that I'm not
your brother, your sister--

00:23:10.230 --> 00:23:13.470
I should be a slave
obeying my master.

00:23:13.470 --> 00:23:15.630
And that is something--

00:23:15.630 --> 00:23:19.530
you all, I don't know you, but
I ain't going to do that, OK?

00:23:19.530 --> 00:23:22.850
And also, I think that's what
gay and lesbian people are

00:23:22.850 --> 00:23:23.350
like.

00:23:23.350 --> 00:23:25.130
OK, you know what,
that's really nice,

00:23:25.130 --> 00:23:28.660
and I hear what you're saying,
but no, because I will not

00:23:28.660 --> 00:23:30.830
be destroyed in that way.

00:23:30.830 --> 00:23:32.830
So anyway, I just
wanted to throw

00:23:32.830 --> 00:23:35.150
that in about interconnectivity
and where we come from.

00:23:35.150 --> 00:23:37.630
It's not just the
political times,

00:23:37.630 --> 00:23:39.820
it is the fundamental
understanding.

00:23:39.820 --> 00:23:41.440
And like I said
to Nick, we're not

00:23:41.440 --> 00:23:43.930
interested in having a
political conversation--

00:23:43.930 --> 00:23:44.907
absolutely boring.

00:23:44.907 --> 00:23:47.490
But we're interested in having
a spiritual conversation, where

00:23:47.490 --> 00:23:49.300
we all are.

00:23:49.300 --> 00:23:52.420
And therefore, there's
grounds for disagreement.

00:23:52.420 --> 00:23:54.130
But yet, brotherhood
and sisterhood,

00:23:54.130 --> 00:23:57.364
that then brings us together
as we're moving forward.

00:23:57.364 --> 00:23:58.780
ANNANDA BARCLAY:
Siblinghood, too.

00:23:58.780 --> 00:23:59.555
FLOYD THOMPKINS: Siblinghood?

00:23:59.555 --> 00:23:59.880
ANNANDA BARCLAY: Siblinghood.

00:23:59.880 --> 00:24:00.546
JANE SPAHR: Yes.

00:24:00.546 --> 00:24:01.412
Evolving.

00:24:01.412 --> 00:24:02.290
FLOYD THOMPKINS:
Evolving siblinghood.

00:24:02.290 --> 00:24:03.706
JANE SPAHR: And
we've all evolved.

00:24:03.706 --> 00:24:08.120
I mean, we have evolved to come
